### wrangler.jsonc / wrangler.toml Configuration

```jsonc
{
  "durable_objects": {
    "bindings": [
      {
        "name": "SYNCED_STATE",        // Must match what you pass to syncedStateRoutes
        "class_name": "SyncedStateServer"
      }
    ]
  },
  "migrations": [
    {
      "tag": "v1",
      "new_classes": ["SyncedStateServer"]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Worker Entry Pattern

```typescript
// worker.tsx
import { defineApp, defineRoutes } from "rwsdk/worker";
import { route, render, except } from "rwsdk/router";
import { syncedStateRoutes, SyncedStateServer } from "rwsdk/use-synced-state/worker";

// Register handlers BEFORE defineApp
SyncedStateServer.registerSetStateHandler((key, value, stub) => {
  // observe state changes
});

const app = defineApp([
  render(Document, [
    // Your page routes
    route("/board/:boardId", ({ params }) => <BoardPage boardId={params.boardId} />),

    // Synced state routes (WebSocket + RPC)
    ...syncedStateRoutes((env) => env.SYNCED_STATE),
  ]),
]);

export default {
  fetch: app.fetch,
};
```

---

## 7. Key Type Signatures

```typescript
// From client-core.d.ts
type SyncedStateStatus = "connected" | "disconnected" | "reconnecting";
type StatusChangeCallback = (status: SyncedStateStatus) => void;

type SyncedStateClient = {
  getState(key: string): Promise<unknown>;
  setState(value: unknown, key: string): Promise<void>;
  subscribe(key: string, handler: (value: unknown) => void): Promise<void>;
  unsubscribe(key: string, handler: (value: unknown) => void): Promise<void>;
};

// From useSyncedState.d.ts
type Setter<T> = (value: T | ((previous: T) => T)) => void;

type CreateSyncedStateHookOptions = {
  url?: string;
  roomId?: string;
  hooks?: HookDeps;
  onStatusChange?: StatusChangeCallback;
};

function createSyncedStateHook(options?: CreateSyncedStateHookOptions):
  <T>(initialValue: T, key: string, roomId?: string) => [T, Setter<T>];

function useSyncedState<T>(initialValue: T, key: string, roomId?: string): [T, Setter<T>];

// From worker.d.mts (SyncedStateServer handlers)
type OnSetHandler = (key: string, value: unknown, stub: DurableObjectStub<SyncedStateServer>) => void;
type OnGetHandler = (key: string, value: unknown | undefined, stub: DurableObjectStub<SyncedStateServer>) => void;
type OnKeyHandler = (key: string, stub: DurableObjectStub<SyncedStateServer>) => Promise<string>;
type OnRoomHandler = (roomId: string | undefined, requestInfo: RequestInfo | null) => Promise<string>;
type OnSubscribeHandler = (key: string, stub: DurableObjectStub<SyncedStateServer>) => void;
type OnUnsubscribeHandler = (key: string, stub: DurableObjectStub<SyncedStateServer>) => void;

// From router.d.ts
type RouteMiddleware<T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> = 
  (requestInfo: T) => MaybePromise<React.JSX.Element | Response | void>;

type RouteDefinition<Path extends string = string, T extends RequestInfo = RequestInfo> = {
  path: string;
  handler: RouteHandler<T> | MethodHandlers<T>;
  layouts?: React.FC<LayoutProps<T>>[];
  readonly __rwPath?: Path;
};

// From requestInfo/types.d.ts
interface RequestInfo<Params = any, AppContext = DefaultAppContext> {
  request: Request;
  path: string;
  params: Params;
  ctx: AppContext;
  rw: RwContext;
  cf: ExecutionContext;
  response: ResponseInit & { headers: Headers };
  isAction: boolean;
}
```

---

## 8. How `useSyncedState` Works Internally

The hook resolves the WebSocket URL based on `roomId`:
- No roomId: connects to `"/__synced-state"` (or custom `url`)
- With roomId: connects to `"/__synced-state/${roomId}"` (or `url/${roomId}`)

On mount:
1. Gets existing state via `client.getState(key)` — if found, updates local state
2. Subscribes via `client.subscribe(key, handler)` for real-time updates
3. On unmount, calls `client.unsubscribe(key, handler)`
4. The `setSyncValue` setter optimistically updates local state AND calls `client.setState(value, key)`

The underlying transport is capnweb (Cap'n Proto over WebSocket) — lazy-loaded so apps not using synced state pay no import cost.

